0th centuries, when these cultural exchanges were most powerfully at work. This work explores the sexual attitudes and activities of those who ran the British Empire. The study explains the pervasive importance of sexuality in the Victorian Empire, both for individuals and as a general dynamic in the working of the system. Among the topics included in the book are prostitution, the manners and mores of missionaries and aspects of race in sexual behaviour.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aStudies in Imperialism 2017. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  aBritish empire.  aIndian prostitutes.  aPurity Campaign.  aVictorian expansion.  achastity.  adecorum.  aeighteenth-century Britain.  aimperial elite.  alal bazar.  amarriage.  amistresses.  asexual attitudes.  asexual dynamics.  asexual opportunism.1 aHyam, Ronald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152611952040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526119520423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526119520/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles